sector.narrative:
Implementing Bangladesh Delta Plan 2100 concerns bringing the long term adaptation to climate change and related water governance approach with multi-sectoral strategic planning and investment ambitions into practice. This means preparing and acting upon the following implementation activities:
- preparing necessary institutional development and arrangements to prepare a dedicated Delta Wing under GED and national Delta Governance Council;
- increasing connective capacity of involved institutions and implementing agencies; participation of stakeholders; 
-  knowledgemanagement and learning by improving the Information Portal and by additional studies;
- increasing the funding capacity for investements considering funding 1) by GoB, Development Partners and IFI's; 2) by PPP investments; 3) by Green Climate Fund;
- adapting the natural systems and processes in the Delta according to BDP2100 strategies and proposed projects. This is done by River Basin Management and basin wise programming with a dedicated decision support system.

description.narrative:
The SIBDP Annual Plan 2022  has been formulated for the remaining project period up to 30 September 2022, with four important aspects in mind:
1.	The results so far and MTR-outcomes;
2.	Working under continued Covid19 conditions;
3.	End of SIBDP-project on 30 September 2022;
4.	Items to be taken up under possible extension.
The SIBDP-project focuses this year on finalization of the expected support and deliverables on the five implementation capacities and on recommendations provided by the MTR.
The Annual Plan 2021 was formulated with the assumption of returning to a ‘normal’ working period in 2021. However, due to Covid19, the SIBDP-activities have in many cases been initiated and coordinated by the TL and DTL in numerous online meetings between team members, with EKN, with GED, BWDB and others. This way of working was the best possible way to make progress under the circumstances. Fortunately, progress could be made during this pandemic period although in a slower pace than foreseen in the Annual Plan 2021 because of travel constraints, working on distance from the team members and also due to the fact that team members have been infected by the Corona virus. This also applies to GED which was given the circumstances not fully operational. Besides, the Member GED has been appointed as State Minister of Planning and the position of Member GED has been vacant for 4 months. Moreover, the Division Chief of GED retired in December. This means that two important and well-informed officials who worked intensely on the BDP2100 right from the start left GED.
The present Annual Plan 2022 contains a number of activities of 2021 which will continue in the remaining project period. This Annual Plan builds on the assumption that normalization of SIBDP-activities may take place in the course of 2022. Findings of the MTR-Report and follow-up actions by SIBDP are elaborated in Chapter 2. Chapter 3 presents the planned actions in 2022 in line with Annual Plan 2021 and based on the Workplan of the Inception Report. Chapter 4 briefly explores risks related to realization of the expected outcomes and indicates possible measures. The financial forecast for the period of January 2022 – September 2022 and the financial outlook for extension have been presented in Chapter 5.
